  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators believe that disclosure of HIV status could influence medication adherence.
      If disclosure leads to social support, adherence could be improved. This study purpose is to
      assess correlation between disclosure and medication adherence, and to describe people whose
      HIV status has been disclosed to.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Pharmacists administer a questionnaire to each consecutive subject taking part in the
      adherence-enhancing program at the pharmacy of the Department of Ambulatory Care And
      Community Medicine in Lausanne. This questionnaire assesses disclosure, response to
      disclosure, and living situation.

      Adherence is measured by electronic monitoring and pill count.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
